physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Physical examination was remarkable for icteric sclera and mild exophthalmos. No lymphadenopathy was found. There were no thyroid abnormalities. The liver span was 11 cm in the midclavicular line, with mild tenderness along the entire palpable liver edge. There was no shifting dullness, and no spleen tip was palpated. She had no asterixis or any signs or symptoms of encephalopathy. No spider angioma was identified.

physical_examinations.changes_over_time: On this date, her ALT level was 940 U/L and total bilirubin was 2.1 mg/dL, indicating a worsening of liver function from previous examinations.
